&gt;&gt;Sheryl: There ya go!

00:04:32.536 --> 00:04:34.836
&gt;&gt;Sheryl: Andi is in my
Critical Thinking class,

00:04:35.006 --> 00:04:36.826
and she's in my Pre-Calculus class.

00:04:37.746 --> 00:04:39.286
She is also my daughter!

00:04:39.996 --> 00:04:44.586
The internship, it's made her a
better student, because of the--

00:04:44.586 --> 00:04:46.746
having more pride and
confidence in herself.

00:04:47.176 --> 00:04:47.456
&gt;&gt;Andi: Go.

00:04:48.426 --> 00:04:53.506
&gt;&gt;Sheryl: And her dream is to open a
tennis club for the underprivileged.

00:04:53.806 --> 00:04:57.506
&gt;&gt;Andi: What's next for me is that
I'm going to either go to college,

00:04:57.506 --> 00:04:58.896
or go play on the pro tour.

00:05:00.006 --> 00:05:03.346
&gt;&gt;Courtney: We want them to
be excited about their passion

00:05:03.346 --> 00:05:05.366
and tie that to their education.

00:05:05.686 --> 00:05:09.046
So they can be successful
lifelong learners.

00:05:09.556 --> 00:05:15.196
&gt;&gt;Laura: Every high school should allow
the space and the place for students

00:05:15.196 --> 00:05:21.266
to explore their passion, even if
it was just for 20 minutes a day.

00:05:21.316 --> 00:05:23.066
Maybe it's 45 minutes a week.

00:05:23.066 --> 00:05:25.786
I think that they would
see some huge benefits.

